The US Equity market has had much more time to evolve than crypto, but w/ that we see many vestiges of the past

Exciting to see teams looking to innovate in a space that has been slow to evolve, and has grown inefficient while technology like blockchain proliferates elsewhere

1) US Eq is complex w/ many hands touching a trade/getting paid
2) Regs evolved around this old system
3) disintermediate complexity - raise bar on client protections 
4) lower bar to become a participant in the market
5) leverage blockchain for realtime custody & clearing

You can still trade IOTX on our USD and EUR books, currently in limit-only. We are evaluating options to provide traders sufficient supply of IOTX on the platform moving forward.
In order to protect traders in the immediate term, Coinbase is aggregating the supply of IOTX-E by pausing trading on our IOTX-USDT and IOTX-BTC books.

Users can still acquire the ERC-20 on Coinbase, but due to the supply/demand disparity, the price is higher than the native IOTX chain token on other exchanges.

Coinbase provides support for the ERC-20 version of IOTX (IOTX-E) which has a more limited supply than the native IOTX chain. The limited supply of ERC-20s means that traders may not be able to acquire sufficient tokens to account for increased demand at market prices.
We have paused trading on our IOTX-USDT and IOTX-BTC pairs due to price disparity compared to other exchange venues.
